description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANTS IN PAEDIATRIC HAEMATOLOGY WITH INTEREST IN:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HAEMOGLOBINOPATHY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are welcomed from enthusiastic and motivated individuals to join the established, friendly team of 7 paediatric haematologists at Birmingham Children’s Hospital (BCH) in our purpose-built Haematology/Oncology unit in “Waterfall House”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A 10 PA post is available in the department. This is a newly created post which has been developed to support the ongoing development of the West Midlands paediatric specialist centre and Haemoglobinopathy Coordinating Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the UK’s largest Paediatric Haematology departments, we see a broad case-mix of both malignant and non-malignant disease and oversee an active clinical programme in all areas of Haematology including: Stem Cell Transplantation, Haemoglobinopathy, Haemato-oncology, and Haemostasis/Thrombosis.The successful applicants will be part of dedicated medical team of 8 Consultants (including this post), 7 Haematology Specialist Registrars/Clinical fellows and 3 ST2/3’s. There are also 7 trained/in training Advanced Nurse Practitioners in our department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Birmingham Women and Children’s NHS Foundation Trust provides secondary and tertiary level paediatric services for the child and adolescent population of much of the city of Birmingham and is the regional referral centre for the West Midlands (population 5.2m).Our core purpose is to lead exceptional services for the health and well-being of every child and young person, and the hospital’s integrated and holistic approach was highlighted as an example of best practice in the recent report from the NHS Future Forum.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will be expected to hold their CCT or be within 6 months of award of CCT in Haematology or General Paediatrics (or equivalent) by the time of interview. The applicant must have the relevant training in Paediatric Haematology. Potential applicants are encouraged to contact us to discuss the advertised job plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange a COVID-secure visit please contact Dr Sarah Lawson (Clinical Lead) or Dr Mark Velangi (Haemoglobinopathy Lead) on 0121 333 9844.&lt;/p&gt;
